# CSS Styling Conventions

## Architecture

- Plain CSS files colocated with their component/page (e.g. `project.tsx` + `project.css`).
- No CSS modules, no CSS-in-JS, no Tailwind. All styling uses vanilla CSS with BEM-like class names.
- Global design tokens and base element styles live in `src/foundation/foundation.css`.

## Naming

Every page/component owns a root class and uses double-underscore for descendants:

```
.project-page              /* root */
.project-page__hero        /* descendant */
.project-page__hero-row    /* deeper descendant (hyphen, not nested __) */
```

Pages use `<page-name>-page` (e.g. `dashboard-page`, `issue-page`).
Components use their own name (e.g. `info-grid`, `issue-table`, `linked-issues-table`).

## Design Tokens

Always reference CSS custom properties from `:root` — never hard-code colors, font sizes, or font families.

Key token families:
- **Colors**: `--color-primary`, `--color-gray1`..`--color-gray9`, `--color-main-bg`, `--color-main-fg`
- **Type scale** (fluid clamp): `--step--2` through `--step-6`
- **Fonts**: `--font-monospace` (body default), `--font-sans`, `--font-serif`
- **Buttons**: `--button-border-radius`, `--button-shadow-color`

Dark mode is handled via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` overrides inside `:root` — do not add a separate dark theme class.

## Recurring Layout Patterns

Pages follow a consistent card-stack layout. When creating a new page or section:

```css
.example-page {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}

.example-page__hero,
.example-page__section {
  background: var(--color-main-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-gray3);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 1.5rem;
}
```

Inset panels (metadata, filters) use the lighter card style:

```css
background: var(--color-gray1);
border: 1px solid var(--color-gray3);
border-radius: 8px;
padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
```

Responsive stacking at `max-width: 40em`:

```css
@media (max-width: 40em) {
  .example-page__hero-row { flex-direction: column; }
}
```

## Buttons

- Solid buttons: use the global `button` / `.button` styles from `foundation.css`. Variants via `.secondary`, `.tertiary`, `.ghost`.
- Page-specific CTA/secondary buttons repeat a shared pattern — keep these consistent:

```css
align-items: center;
border-radius: 4px;
display: inline-flex;
font-weight: 700;
min-height: 2.75rem;
padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
text-decoration: none;
```

## Tables

Use the `issue-table` pattern: full-width, `border-collapse: collapse`, uppercase `th` labels (`--step--1`, `letter-spacing: 0.03em`), `--color-gray3` row borders, hover row highlight with `--color-gray1`.

## Typography in Components

- Muted/secondary text: `color: var(--color-gray8)`.
- Labels/captions: `font-size: var(--step--1); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase`.
- Never set `font-family` on individual components — the body inherits `--font-monospace`.
